column3:
> Drop unneeded double-quoting (which we use inconsistently), use `[]` for empty arguments, space things out.

Concept ACK, obviously, as I'm using the same style :)

Why update Autoconf macros as they have no functional changes?
Mostly concept ACK. Checked (only) http://git.savannah.gnu.org/gitweb/?p=autoconf-archive.git;a=blob_plain;f=m4/ax_check_preproc_flag.m4 to see licensing changes come from upstream.\n

> Why update Autoconf macros as they have no functional changes?\n\nMostly just why not, and if we do it now, it saves someone else wanting to do it in the future. I'd think that these files will be very unlikely to be ever updated again after this.
Concept ACK, will at least check for binary identity soon.
